    // test-record transport rides the child's stderr; the runner demuxes
    // stdout(user) + stderr(records) via `io.poll_any` over the two raw
    // fds, so it needs accessors for those fds (`handle_stdout_fd` /
    // `handle_stderr_fd`), a stderr counterpart of the framed-stdout
    // chunk read (`handle_read_bytes_stderr`), the stderr EOF predicate
    // (`handle_stderr_at_eof`), and a handle-owned deadline kill
    // (`handle_kill`, SIGKILL) that retires the outer `timeout(1)`
    // wrapper. Same Sailfin-native bodies + always-declare pattern as the
    // framed-stdout cluster above (`runtime/sfn/process.sfn`); the cross-
    // windows path resolves them from the degraded stubs in
